# Open Source Dashboard — AI/LLMs/Automation

A beautiful local web dashboard that helps Can discover, track, and contribute to open source projects in the AI/LLMs/Automation space.

## What It Does

The dashboard has **4 sections**:

1. **📊 Your GitHub Profile** — Stats, repos, languages, contribution activity
2. **🔥 Trending AI Repos** — Hot repos in AI/LLM/automation right now (via GitHub API)
3. **🏷️ Good First Issues** — Beginner-friendly issues in top AI repos you could tackle
4. **🗺️ Learning Roadmap** — Curated list of AI/automation repos organized by difficulty

## Tech Stack

- **HTML + CSS + JavaScript** — Single-page app, no frameworks needed
- **GitHub API** via `gh` CLI — Fetches live data
- **Shell scripts** — Generate the data that the dashboard displays
- **Local web server** — Just open the HTML file or use a simple server

This keeps it **simple and beginner-friendly** — no npm installs, no build steps, just files that work.

## Proposed Changes

### Data Layer

#### [NEW] [fetch-data.sh](file:///Users/canerden/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/opensource-dashboard/fetch-data.sh)

A shell script that uses `gh` CLI to fetch:
- User profile stats (repos, followers, stars)
- List of user's own repos with languages
- Trending repos from GitHub (AI/LLM/automation topics)
- Good first issues from popular AI repos (langchain, ollama, n8n, huggingface, etc.)
- Saves all data as JSON files in a `data/` folder

### Dashboard UI

#### [NEW] [index.html](file:///Users/canerden/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/opensource-dashboard/index.html)

Main dashboard page with 4 cards/sections:
- Profile overview with stats
- Trending repos carousel
- Good first issues list with filters
- Learning roadmap with difficulty levels

#### [NEW] [style.css](file:///Users/canerden/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/opensource-dashboard/style.css)

Dark-themed, modern design with:
- Glassmorphism cards
- Gradient accents (purple/blue AI theme)
- Smooth animations
- Fully responsive

#### [NEW] [app.js](file:///Users/canerden/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/opensource-dashboard/app.js)

Loads JSON data and renders the dashboard sections. Handles:
- Loading/displaying data
- Filtering issues by label/repo
- Sorting trending repos
- External links to GitHub repos/issues

### Launcher

#### [NEW] [run.sh](file:///Users/canerden/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/opensource-dashboard/run.sh)

One-command launcher:
```bash
./run.sh
```
This will:
1. Fetch fresh data from GitHub
2. Open the dashboard in your browser

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Run `./fetch-data.sh` and verify JSON files are created in `data/`
- Open `index.html` in the browser and visually verify all 4 sections display correctly

### Manual Verification
- Open the dashboard in the browser
- Verify your GitHub profile stats match your actual profile
- Click on trending repo links and verify they go to the correct GitHub pages
- Click on issue links and verify they open the right issues
- Check that the design looks good on different screen sizes
